freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: New extremely accelerated neuropathy terrible spasms in left ankle all night. Made me wake and cry out each time. May not be related to my possible mild case of COVID in early August or my vaccine. Have had neuropathy for few years but this is new.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: I should have mentioned sooner but I have a very mild dry cough since August that is not too bad.

Left cervical tender swollen lymph node. In early August had brief fever 101.3 then red hot skin above ankles , then top of left foot darkened and some of toes considerably darkened. Took many months to go away. Top of foot still slightly dark. At time we were not told to watch for such symptoms. No doctor saw.  Was not sick. Fever only lasted a a few hours. Took Tylenol.
